1
00:01:37,039 --> 00:01:40,140
[Born to Be Alive]

2
00:01:40,170 --> 00:01:43,130
[Episode 14]

3
00:01:43,229 --> 00:01:44,289
Even talking about

4
00:01:44,720 --> 00:01:46,320
solving personal problems.

5
00:01:46,509 --> 00:01:46,979
Mom,

6
00:01:47,620 --> 00:01:49,020
you're overthinking it.

7
00:01:51,400 --> 00:01:53,460
I think you're the one overthinking.

8
00:01:55,880 --> 00:01:57,210
Don't bring it up later.

9
00:01:59,259 --> 00:01:59,720
Eat more.

10
00:01:59,720 --> 00:02:00,510
There's plenty left.

11
00:02:00,510 --> 00:02:01,010
Eat.

12
00:02:03,230 --> 00:02:03,930
Is it good?

13
00:02:04,700 --> 00:02:05,630
It's delicious.

14
00:02:07,300 --> 00:02:07,950
How is the taste

15
00:02:07,950 --> 00:02:09,410
different from last time?

16
00:02:15,430 --> 00:02:16,980
There's not much difference.

17
00:02:16,980 --> 00:02:17,740
It's lamb.

18
00:02:19,070 --> 00:02:20,470
I knew you couldn't tell.

19
00:02:20,740 --> 00:02:21,200
Really?

20
00:02:32,400 --> 00:02:33,520
Why are you sitting here?

21
00:02:33,520 --> 00:02:34,030
Shao.

22
00:02:34,310 --> 00:02:35,630
you look like a little old lady.

23
00:02:35,630 --> 00:02:36,120
If you can't speak nicely,

24
00:02:36,120 --> 00:02:37,180
then shut up.

25
00:02:37,620 --> 00:02:39,420
I'm having some alone time here.

26
00:02:39,740 --> 00:02:40,250
How come you two

27
00:02:40,250 --> 00:02:40,980
came back together?

28
00:02:40,980 --> 00:02:41,470
I went shopping,

29
00:02:41,470 --> 00:02:42,079
didn't I?

30
00:02:42,180 --> 00:02:42,860
I met Han,

31
00:02:42,920 --> 00:02:44,050
and he gave me a ride.

32
00:02:44,150 --> 00:02:44,750
Big Sister.

33
00:02:44,750 --> 00:02:45,280
I'm here to pick up

34
00:02:45,280 --> 00:02:46,370
Bai Ju and Shao.

35
00:02:46,460 --> 00:02:48,150
Who are you calling Big Sister?

36
00:02:48,150 --> 00:02:49,410
Look at how old you are.

37
00:02:49,900 --> 00:02:50,960
Don't call me that.

38
00:02:51,240 --> 00:02:52,300
What did you go buy?

39
00:02:52,700 --> 00:02:54,230
Come on, let's talk inside.

40
00:02:54,760 --> 00:02:56,370
Don't pull on my clothes.

41
00:02:56,400 --> 00:02:57,350
If this gets dirty,

42
00:02:57,350 --> 00:02:58,350
it'll be a hassle.

43
00:02:58,750 --> 00:02:59,860
You can't wash it with water.

44
00:02:59,860 --> 00:03:01,320
What kind of clothes can't get wet?

45
00:03:01,320 --> 00:03:02,380
Is it made of paper?

46
00:03:03,180 --> 00:03:04,970
It's cashmere. Do you know what that is?

47
00:03:04,970 --> 00:03:06,120
Mom, Ju.

48
00:03:07,210 --> 00:03:08,070
Fei is here too.

49
00:03:09,130 --> 00:03:09,620
Han.

50
00:03:09,930 --> 00:03:10,700
Come, perfect timing.

51
00:03:10,700 --> 00:03:11,550
Eat. Sit down.

52
00:03:11,580 --> 00:03:12,210
Director Zhang,

53
00:03:12,210 --> 00:03:12,900
Han.

54
00:03:13,000 --> 00:03:14,190
You're having dumplings?

55
00:03:14,190 --> 00:03:14,950
I won't eat then.

56
00:03:14,950 --> 00:03:15,310
You guys go ahead.

57
00:03:15,310 --> 00:03:15,780
Eat.

58
00:03:16,460 --> 00:03:18,090
We made vegetarian ones just for you.

59
00:03:18,090 --> 00:03:19,190
Mom made them for you.

60
00:03:19,190 --> 00:03:20,090
Thank you, Director Zhang.

61
00:03:20,090 --> 00:03:21,030
Thank you, Director Zhang.

62
00:03:21,030 --> 00:03:21,760
Give it to me.

63
00:03:22,950 --> 00:03:24,200
You always walk in

64
00:03:24,370 --> 00:03:25,440
right on time.

65
00:03:25,460 --> 00:03:26,960
You don't do any work at all.

66
00:03:26,960 --> 00:03:28,380
Didn't I go shopping?

67
00:03:29,070 --> 00:03:29,750
You can't save a penny

68
00:03:29,750 --> 00:03:31,240
of the money you earn.

69
00:03:31,870 --> 00:03:33,150
This is called investment.

70
00:03:33,150 --> 00:03:33,900
It's for my future success.

71
00:03:33,900 --> 00:03:35,460
It's worth it.

72
00:03:37,090 --> 00:03:38,220
I've made up my mind.

73
00:03:38,750 --> 00:03:40,150
I'll follow Uncle Lin's arrangement

74
00:03:40,150 --> 00:03:40,930
and go to Tanggula

75
00:03:40,930 --> 00:03:42,730
to be a road maintenance worker.

76
00:03:50,020 --> 00:03:51,340
The conditions at the maintenance depot

77
00:03:51,340 --> 00:03:52,870
are very harsh.

78
00:03:53,800 --> 00:03:55,530
You have to think this through.

79
00:03:57,060 --> 00:03:57,430
Well,

80
00:03:58,670 --> 00:04:00,000
I even went to Bolamula.

81
00:04:00,930 --> 00:04:03,130
No matter how hard it is, I can handle it.

82
00:04:03,250 --> 00:04:04,710
That's a different story.

83
00:04:05,530 --> 00:04:07,390
The work at Tanggula is a long haul.

84
00:04:07,390 --> 00:04:09,650
You won't be back
for six months to a year.

85
00:04:09,710 --> 00:04:10,760
The altitude there

86
00:04:10,760 --> 00:04:11,690
is 5,000 or 6,000 meters.

87
00:04:11,690 --> 00:04:12,400
I know.

88
00:04:12,420 --> 00:04:13,030
I've already bought

89
00:04:13,030 --> 00:04:14,130
everything I need to prepare

90
00:04:14,130 --> 00:04:15,040
in advance.

91
00:04:17,269 --> 00:04:17,720
Look.

92
00:04:18,310 --> 00:04:18,870
Gloves.

93
00:04:20,390 --> 00:04:21,589
These are wool socks.

94
00:04:25,070 --> 00:04:25,680
Knee pads.

95
00:04:26,650 --> 00:04:27,230
And this.

96
00:04:28,160 --> 00:04:29,780
High-altitude protective cream.

97
00:04:29,780 --> 00:04:30,770
Compared to what Guo gave me,

98
00:04:30,770 --> 00:04:32,040
it definitely isn't as great,

99
00:04:32,040 --> 00:04:33,300
but it's still usable.

100
00:04:34,270 --> 00:04:34,980
And this,

101
00:04:36,570 --> 00:04:37,690
Yan insisted I take it.

102
00:04:37,690 --> 00:04:38,250
Rhodiola Rosea

103
00:04:38,250 --> 00:04:40,050
I've already started taking it.

104
00:04:40,800 --> 00:04:42,310
Don't think that just because Uncle Lin

105
00:04:42,310 --> 00:04:43,770
arranged this job for you,

106
00:04:43,770 --> 00:04:44,640
you have to go to save face.

107
00:04:44,640 --> 00:04:45,390
It's not about saving face.

108
00:04:45,390 --> 00:04:46,360
I know Uncle Lin

109
00:04:46,390 --> 00:04:47,390
means well.

110
00:04:47,920 --> 00:04:48,720
I'll stay there,

111
00:04:48,720 --> 00:04:49,690
and stick it out for three months.

112
00:04:49,690 --> 00:04:50,360
After I pass the probation period,

113
00:04:50,360 --> 00:04:51,620
I'll work for another year,

114
00:04:51,620 --> 00:04:52,159
and I might be able

115
00:04:52,159 --> 00:04:54,460
to transfer to another maintenance depot.

116
00:04:54,460 --> 00:04:56,120
I'll work hard the first year,

117
00:04:56,680 --> 00:04:57,940
and try to get an award.

118
00:05:03,440 --> 00:05:04,500
I swear I'll change

119
00:05:04,510 --> 00:05:05,390
and be a new man.

120
00:05:07,620 --> 00:05:08,740
Take this back.

121
00:05:09,170 --> 00:05:10,230
Once you're there,

122
00:05:10,450 --> 00:05:11,150
there probably won't be

123
00:05:11,150 --> 00:05:12,660
any entertainment anyway.

124
00:05:12,660 --> 00:05:14,830
I'm quitting gaming.

125
00:05:15,530 --> 00:05:16,450
Give this to Tashi.

126
00:05:16,450 --> 00:05:17,160
He likes it.

127
00:05:17,590 --> 00:05:19,050
When I get there, I'll just

128
00:05:19,570 --> 00:05:20,420
read books

129
00:05:20,510 --> 00:05:22,080
and gain knowledge.

130
00:05:22,100 --> 00:05:22,870
Don't.

131
00:05:23,270 --> 00:05:24,070
The altitude is so high,

132
00:05:24,070 --> 00:05:25,930
you'll get a headache if you read.

133
00:05:26,100 --> 00:05:27,330
He gets a headache reading

134
00:05:27,330 --> 00:05:28,580
even at low altitudes.

135
00:05:28,580 --> 00:05:29,580
Shao.

136
00:05:29,770 --> 00:05:30,830
I'm not wrong, am I?

137
00:05:31,220 --> 00:05:32,450
I-I'm bringing

138
00:05:32,470 --> 00:05:33,310
all of the Four Classic Novels.

139
00:05:33,310 --> 00:05:34,220
I'll just read book

140
00:05:34,220 --> 00:05:35,150
and study there.

141
00:05:36,380 --> 00:05:38,590
Maybe just take one for now.

142
00:05:40,330 --> 00:05:41,010
Bai Ji.

143
00:05:44,140 --> 00:05:45,740
A gift for starting your job.

144
00:05:50,659 --> 00:05:51,480
Thanks, Shao.

145
00:06:05,040 --> 00:06:05,650
Don't worry.

146
00:06:05,650 --> 00:06:06,570
I'll work hard.

147
00:06:10,720 --> 00:06:11,330
Let's eat.

148
00:06:11,370 --> 00:06:12,700
Stop analyzing me. Eat.

149
00:06:16,820 --> 00:06:18,430
Director, is there dumpling soup?

150
00:06:18,430 --> 00:06:19,060
Yes.

151
00:06:19,160 --> 00:06:20,260
It's in the pot. Help yourself.

152
00:06:20,260 --> 00:06:20,540
I'll go.

153
00:06:20,540 --> 00:06:21,160
Me too.

154
00:06:29,000 --> 00:06:29,790
What is this?

155
00:06:29,930 --> 00:06:31,500
What kind of dumpling is this?

156
00:06:31,500 --> 00:06:32,440
It's lamb.

157
00:06:32,540 --> 00:06:34,140
This isn't grass-fed, is it?

158
00:06:35,930 --> 00:06:37,159
Just eat what you're given.

159
00:06:37,159 --> 00:06:38,180
You talk too much.

160
00:06:46,200 --> 00:06:47,460
Danzhou stole my notes

161
00:06:47,800 --> 00:06:49,830
to do mineral exploration in Bolamula.

162
00:06:49,830 --> 00:06:50,810
What's going on?

163
00:06:51,540 --> 00:06:53,270
What do you mean by "your notes"?

164
00:06:53,270 --> 00:06:54,010
You were

165
00:06:54,040 --> 00:06:54,740
using the county's money

166
00:06:54,740 --> 00:06:55,600
to do this work.

167
00:06:56,270 --> 00:06:57,070
Now it's you

168
00:06:57,090 --> 00:06:58,070
who refuses to carry out
mineral exploration.

169
00:06:58,070 --> 00:06:59,370
And you didn't submit
the previous reports either.

170
00:06:59,370 --> 00:07:00,600
So if someone else uses these notes

171
00:07:00,600 --> 00:07:01,660
to carry out the work, is there a problem?

172
00:07:01,660 --> 00:07:02,720
Of course there is.

173
00:07:04,000 --> 00:07:05,330
The area for mineral exploration

174
00:07:05,330 --> 00:07:06,830
and the Tibetan antelope migration route

175
00:07:06,830 --> 00:07:08,160
overlap in one section.

176
00:07:08,430 --> 00:07:09,450
Even if you want to do
mineral exploration,

177
00:07:09,450 --> 00:07:11,310
it shouldn't be done in this area.

178
00:07:12,560 --> 00:07:13,090
Since you

179
00:07:13,100 --> 00:07:14,040
took my notes,

180
00:07:14,390 --> 00:07:16,390
why didn't you read them carefully?

181
00:07:18,510 --> 00:07:19,570
Mining in this area

182
00:07:20,570 --> 00:07:22,480
overlaps with
the Tibetan antelope migration.

183
00:07:22,480 --> 00:07:23,540
Mining in that area

184
00:07:23,560 --> 00:07:24,740
encroaches on the Tibetan antelope's

185
00:07:24,740 --> 00:07:25,670
mating grounds.

186
00:07:25,930 --> 00:07:26,830
And another area

187
00:07:26,830 --> 00:07:27,740
could potentially pollute

188
00:07:27,740 --> 00:07:28,470
the nearby water sources.

189
00:07:28,470 --> 00:07:29,270
That's right.

190
00:07:29,870 --> 00:07:31,400
Didn't you memorize it all?

191
00:07:32,650 --> 00:07:33,980
If we follow your notes,

192
00:07:34,340 --> 00:07:36,940
I won't be able to build
this development zone.

193
00:07:37,420 --> 00:07:38,300
Your development zone

194
00:07:38,300 --> 00:07:40,430
shouldn't be built in the first place.

195
00:07:40,610 --> 00:07:41,720
The superiors haven't approved it yet

196
00:07:41,720 --> 00:07:43,130
and you're already running
a pilot project,

197
00:07:43,130 --> 00:07:44,900
violating organizational procedures.

198
00:07:44,900 --> 00:07:45,960
I could report you.

199
00:08:09,480 --> 00:08:10,010
Go ahead.

200
00:08:10,680 --> 00:08:11,680
[Letter of Report]

201
00:08:11,800 --> 00:08:12,680
If you think

202
00:08:12,750 --> 00:08:13,570
replacing me

203
00:08:13,720 --> 00:08:14,650
is good for Mazhi County

204
00:08:14,650 --> 00:08:15,950
and good for the people,

205
00:08:15,950 --> 00:08:17,210
then go ahead and do it.

206
00:08:28,550 --> 00:08:29,110
Wait.

207
00:08:35,080 --> 00:08:35,940
Close the door.

208
00:08:51,110 --> 00:08:51,710
Take this.

209
00:09:01,200 --> 00:09:02,260
What are you doing?

210
00:09:02,910 --> 00:09:03,570
Bribing me?

211
00:09:04,060 --> 00:09:05,390
I really can report you.

212
00:09:06,420 --> 00:09:08,480
Madam Zhu asked me to give this to you.

213
00:09:11,400 --> 00:09:11,870
Did you

214
00:09:11,890 --> 00:09:12,810
mortgage the pasture?

215
00:09:12,810 --> 00:09:13,730
Is that true?

216
00:09:18,750 --> 00:09:19,610
I won't take it.

217
00:09:20,130 --> 00:09:21,600
Let's keep things separate.

218
00:09:21,600 --> 00:09:22,800
Don't be so stubborn.

219
00:09:22,890 --> 00:09:23,440
If you keep this up,

220
00:09:23,440 --> 00:09:23,980
even if Cairen doesn't scold you,

221
00:09:23,980 --> 00:09:24,930
I will.

222
00:09:26,220 --> 00:09:26,720
Take it.

223
00:09:33,290 --> 00:09:33,980
Thank you.

224
00:09:34,990 --> 00:09:36,050
But I don't want it.

225
00:09:42,950 --> 00:09:44,350
Deputy County Mayor Duo.

226
00:09:45,130 --> 00:09:46,530
Deputy County Mayor Duo.

227
00:09:46,670 --> 00:09:47,600
Deputy County Mayor Duo.

228
00:09:47,600 --> 00:09:48,860
Tell him I don't want it.

229
00:09:48,860 --> 00:09:49,860
It's gas coupons.

230
00:09:53,170 --> 00:09:55,630
County Mayor Lin asked me
to give them to you.

231
00:10:14,260 --> 00:10:15,410
As for the silver mine pilot project,

232
00:10:15,410 --> 00:10:17,740
I'll have Danzhou find another location.

233
00:10:23,140 --> 00:10:27,250
[Ethnic]

234
00:10:32,160 --> 00:10:33,260
Twenty-five liters.

235
00:10:33,260 --> 00:10:33,920
Just right.

236
00:10:34,360 --> 00:10:34,740
Okay.

237
00:10:36,040 --> 00:10:37,040
Fifty-five yuan.

238
00:10:37,550 --> 00:10:38,340
Bai, pay him.

239
00:10:41,910 --> 00:10:43,770
He Qingyuan is really something.

240
00:10:43,790 --> 00:10:45,320
He even schemed against me.

241
00:10:46,530 --> 00:10:48,200
Next time you say you're out of gas,

242
00:10:48,200 --> 00:10:50,200
you can ride a horse back to the team.

243
00:10:50,540 --> 00:10:51,080
Exactly.

244
00:10:56,920 --> 00:10:58,040
What's so urgent?

245
00:10:58,820 --> 00:11:00,150
Do you have to call here?

246
00:11:00,820 --> 00:11:02,440
Can't you call back at the station?

247
00:11:02,440 --> 00:11:03,720
Isn't it good?

248
00:11:04,340 --> 00:11:05,410
It saves us money.

249
00:11:06,440 --> 00:11:08,240
More sensible than He Qingyuan.

250
00:11:09,690 --> 00:11:10,290
You two have

251
00:11:10,290 --> 00:11:11,820
a life-and-death bond now.

252
00:11:12,670 --> 00:11:13,600
Why is it that...

253
00:11:17,990 --> 00:11:19,120
The look in your eyes

254
00:11:19,650 --> 00:11:21,710
is getting more and more like Duojie?

255
00:11:24,670 --> 00:11:25,280
Is it?

256
00:11:25,530 --> 00:11:26,080
Yes.

257
00:11:27,120 --> 00:11:27,530
It is.

258
00:11:30,370 --> 00:11:31,780
I just called the person in charge

259
00:11:31,780 --> 00:11:32,780
of the paper mill.

260
00:11:33,030 --> 00:11:33,890
About the toilet paper,

261
00:11:33,890 --> 00:11:35,200
I'm really grateful to them.

262
00:11:35,200 --> 00:11:36,090
They also think

263
00:11:36,120 --> 00:11:36,650
this is very meaningful.

264
00:11:36,650 --> 00:11:37,630
They want me to write a report

265
00:11:37,630 --> 00:11:38,490
for publicity.

266
00:11:38,720 --> 00:11:39,070
I think this is...

267
00:11:39,070 --> 00:11:39,870
Who asked you?

268
00:11:40,050 --> 00:11:40,630
Get in.

269
00:11:59,870 --> 00:12:01,230
You're all back.

270
00:12:02,610 --> 00:12:03,940
Not bad.

271
00:12:04,050 --> 00:12:04,820
Zhacuo.

272
00:12:05,630 --> 00:12:06,500
You're tough.

273
00:12:06,530 --> 00:12:07,790
You recovered so fast.

274
00:12:07,890 --> 00:12:08,740
I'm nothing.

275
00:12:08,760 --> 00:12:09,460
Look at the guy

276
00:12:09,460 --> 00:12:10,460
inside the room.

277
00:12:10,980 --> 00:12:12,040
The one in the room?

278
00:12:19,830 --> 00:12:21,290
Captain, thick or thin noodles?

279
00:12:21,290 --> 00:12:22,820
I'll eat whatever you make.

280
00:12:23,390 --> 00:12:24,510
Thin ones, then.

281
00:12:24,620 --> 00:12:25,130
Okay.

282
00:12:27,270 --> 00:12:28,000
You're back.

283
00:12:30,890 --> 00:12:31,490
How is it?

284
00:12:34,560 --> 00:12:36,190
Ju, you guys are back.

285
00:12:36,310 --> 00:12:37,000
We're back.

286
00:12:38,200 --> 00:12:39,270
Nice.

287
00:12:41,770 --> 00:12:42,270
Han.

288
00:12:42,290 --> 00:12:43,000
Thick or thin?

289
00:12:43,000 --> 00:12:44,400
The usual. Thick.

290
00:12:44,680 --> 00:12:45,610
Coming right up.

291
00:12:47,950 --> 00:12:49,850
Luckily, your hypothermia wasn't severe.

292
00:12:49,850 --> 00:12:52,450
Otherwise, you wouldn't
be eating this ramen.

293
00:12:54,660 --> 00:12:55,920
Careful, it's hot, Ju.

294
00:12:57,760 --> 00:12:58,490
Let me try it.

295
00:13:04,170 --> 00:13:05,070
It's delicious.

296
00:13:05,070 --> 00:13:06,530
Better than my brother's.

297
00:13:08,260 --> 00:13:09,330
With your skills,

298
00:13:09,440 --> 00:13:10,970
you could open a ramen shop.

299
00:13:11,460 --> 00:13:12,900
I can actually cook other things.

300
00:13:12,900 --> 00:13:13,760
Not just ramen.

301
00:13:14,290 --> 00:13:14,770
Really?

302
00:13:15,120 --> 00:13:16,770
Then make something different next time.

303
00:13:16,770 --> 00:13:17,330
Although the ramen

304
00:13:17,330 --> 00:13:18,150
is pretty good too.

305
00:13:18,150 --> 00:13:19,950
this is the third time having it.

306
00:13:20,640 --> 00:13:21,360
But here,

307
00:13:21,390 --> 00:13:22,770
you only have these ingredients.

308
00:13:22,770 --> 00:13:23,580
Even if I want to cook something else,

309
00:13:23,580 --> 00:13:24,320
I can't.

310
00:13:25,910 --> 00:13:27,650
One can't make bricks without straw.

311
00:13:27,650 --> 00:13:28,480
I think

312
00:13:28,550 --> 00:13:29,520
we don't need to pool money

313
00:13:29,520 --> 00:13:30,860
to buy Zhang Yang a ticket home.

314
00:13:30,860 --> 00:13:32,120
He can make money faster than we can

315
00:13:32,120 --> 00:13:33,120
by selling ramen.

316
00:13:33,940 --> 00:13:36,000
Deputy Captain, you're just stingy.

317
00:13:36,100 --> 00:13:37,420
Since you're not stingy,
you can contribute more.

318
00:13:37,420 --> 00:13:37,990
I...

319
00:13:38,540 --> 00:13:39,400
Let me tell you,

320
00:13:39,750 --> 00:13:41,480
we still need to pool the money.

321
00:13:41,820 --> 00:13:43,020
I'll pay two-thirds.

322
00:13:43,170 --> 00:13:43,650
The rest,

323
00:13:43,650 --> 00:13:44,940
based on your salaries,

324
00:13:44,940 --> 00:13:45,890
will be split proportionally.

325
00:13:45,890 --> 00:13:47,080
The newspaper office pays well.

326
00:13:47,080 --> 00:13:48,080
I can chip in more.

327
00:13:48,550 --> 00:13:50,080
Then you guys pay for it all.

328
00:13:50,080 --> 00:13:50,520
No, no.

329
00:13:50,550 --> 00:13:51,410
You have to pay.

330
00:13:52,930 --> 00:13:54,100
Can I not leave?

331
00:13:59,420 --> 00:14:01,880
I don't want to go back to Xunzhong
like this.

332
00:14:03,750 --> 00:14:04,530
I want to stay.

333
00:14:04,530 --> 00:14:06,480
I'll cook and do laundry for you.

334
00:14:09,130 --> 00:14:10,180
I want to go into the mountains with you

335
00:14:10,180 --> 00:14:11,240
to find my brother.

336
00:14:19,570 --> 00:14:20,130
Aren't you also

337
00:14:20,130 --> 00:14:21,460
catching gold diggers?

338
00:14:21,600 --> 00:14:22,290
Maybe I can

339
00:14:22,310 --> 00:14:23,440
provide some clues.

340
00:14:27,750 --> 00:14:28,810
I think that works.

341
00:14:29,480 --> 00:14:30,340
Okay, sure.

342
00:14:30,740 --> 00:14:31,030
Okay.

343
00:14:31,030 --> 00:14:32,160
Thank you, Captain.

344
00:14:32,760 --> 00:14:34,220
I'll get more noodle soup.

345
00:14:40,090 --> 00:14:40,710
Duojie.

346
00:14:41,620 --> 00:14:42,310
Duojie.

347
00:14:46,100 --> 00:14:46,720
Duojie.

348
00:14:48,200 --> 00:14:49,130
Why are you here?

349
00:14:50,140 --> 00:14:51,000
What happened?

350
00:14:57,850 --> 00:14:59,050
Sister-in-law, come and have some noodles.

351
00:14:59,050 --> 00:14:59,770
I'll tie up the horse.

352
00:14:59,770 --> 00:15:00,270
I'll go.

353
00:15:20,640 --> 00:15:21,310
Zhacuo.

354
00:15:22,520 --> 00:15:23,530
Stop feeding the horse.

355
00:15:23,530 --> 00:15:24,800
It'll be stuffed.

356
00:15:25,220 --> 00:15:25,980
Horses aren't stupid.

357
00:15:25,980 --> 00:15:27,580
They know when they're full.

358
00:15:33,220 --> 00:15:34,350
Go and have a listen.

359
00:15:34,410 --> 00:15:35,410
If they start fighting,

360
00:15:35,410 --> 00:15:36,320
we'll go break it up.

361
00:15:36,320 --> 00:15:37,320
-Okay.
-Go ahead.

362
00:15:40,560 --> 00:15:41,490
Why don't you go?

363
00:15:47,250 --> 00:15:48,150
Tashi ran away.

364
00:15:50,140 --> 00:15:51,160
Where did he go?

365
00:15:51,770 --> 00:15:54,300
He went to Zhacuo's house\
to help herd sheep.

366
00:15:54,820 --> 00:15:56,290
He said that

367
00:15:56,320 --> 00:15:57,300
since you sold the field and sheep,

368
00:15:57,300 --> 00:15:58,960
he wouldn't come back either.

369
00:16:01,120 --> 00:16:01,920
Now both of you

370
00:16:01,930 --> 00:16:02,890
are hiding away.

371
00:16:03,360 --> 00:16:03,840
I'll go back

372
00:16:03,840 --> 00:16:05,240
to Mom's house tomorrow.

373
00:16:05,290 --> 00:16:07,050
Let the livestock run away.

374
00:16:09,030 --> 00:16:09,890
How about this.

375
00:16:11,310 --> 00:16:12,970
I'll go explain it to Basang.

376
00:16:14,340 --> 00:16:15,020
They probably won't

377
00:16:15,020 --> 00:16:15,980
kick us out

378
00:16:16,010 --> 00:16:17,540
just for ten thousand yuan.

379
00:16:18,080 --> 00:16:19,680
We're relatives, after all.

380
00:16:20,290 --> 00:16:21,570
You won't even pay back

381
00:16:21,600 --> 00:16:22,530
your relatives.

382
00:16:22,700 --> 00:16:24,470
It's humiliating if word gets out.

383
00:16:24,470 --> 00:16:25,250
Alright.

384
00:16:27,250 --> 00:16:29,180
Worst case, we sell the livestock.

385
00:16:30,790 --> 00:16:31,650
If we sell them,

386
00:16:31,950 --> 00:16:33,520
what will Tashi and I eat?

387
00:16:34,510 --> 00:16:36,070
The cattle and sheep for next year,

388
00:16:36,070 --> 00:16:37,470
how will we deliver them?

389
00:16:39,840 --> 00:16:41,570
I didn't say we'd sell them all.

390
00:16:43,010 --> 00:16:43,730
Just half.

391
00:16:44,980 --> 00:16:45,700
We only have

392
00:16:45,730 --> 00:16:47,060
a few head of livestock.

393
00:16:47,440 --> 00:16:49,170
Other families have herds
of cattle and sheep

394
00:16:49,170 --> 00:16:51,230
while our family lives like beggars.

395
00:16:51,250 --> 00:16:52,570
And we’re supposed to be officials?

396
00:16:52,570 --> 00:16:54,230
We’re worse off than beggars.

397
00:16:54,600 --> 00:16:54,870
You and your reluctance to sell.

398
00:16:54,870 --> 00:16:56,440
[Reluctance to sell: herdsmen compare herd sizes,
and are reluctant to sell their livestock]

399
00:16:56,440 --> 00:16:57,100
I've criticized you before.

400
00:16:57,100 --> 00:16:57,980
Don't talk to me

401
00:16:58,030 --> 00:16:59,030
about ideals.

402
00:16:59,150 --> 00:17:00,410
I just want my pasture.

403
00:17:00,460 --> 00:17:01,100
Without the pasture,

404
00:17:01,100 --> 00:17:02,270
where will we live?

405
00:17:13,630 --> 00:17:14,790
We built that house with our own hands

406
00:17:14,790 --> 00:17:16,250
when we first got married.

407
00:17:16,960 --> 00:17:19,089
We even made the furniture ourselves.

408
00:17:20,200 --> 00:17:21,770
You insisted on painting

409
00:17:22,270 --> 00:17:24,599
the Four Auspicious Signs on the cabinet.

410
00:17:25,420 --> 00:17:26,700
You said for a family,

411
00:17:27,170 --> 00:17:28,630
no matter the conditions,

412
00:17:29,790 --> 00:17:32,990
the most important thing is
that our hearts are together.

413
00:17:33,570 --> 00:17:34,760
But now?

414
00:17:36,620 --> 00:17:37,790
You just casually

415
00:17:37,820 --> 00:17:39,880
mortgaged this home to someone else.

416
00:17:39,940 --> 00:17:41,810
Why didn't you ask me?

417
00:17:46,190 --> 00:17:46,650
Didn't I

418
00:17:46,680 --> 00:17:48,050
tell you before?

419
00:17:49,180 --> 00:17:50,050
Our lives will become better

420
00:17:50,050 --> 00:17:51,220
in the future.

421
00:17:52,030 --> 00:17:53,180
We will have bread.

422
00:17:55,960 --> 00:17:57,200
What about now?

423
00:17:59,070 --> 00:18:00,110
Do you know how hard

424
00:18:00,110 --> 00:18:01,400
it is for me right now?

425
00:18:03,850 --> 00:18:05,450
Who isn't having a hard time?

426
00:18:06,110 --> 00:18:07,390
Every brother in the team

427
00:18:07,390 --> 00:18:09,120
has it harder at home than we do.

428
00:18:10,440 --> 00:18:12,240
Don't talk to me about hardship.

429
00:18:18,770 --> 00:18:19,330
I originally

430
00:18:19,330 --> 00:18:20,570
supported your work.

431
00:18:21,480 --> 00:18:22,880
You want to do big things,

432
00:18:23,500 --> 00:18:25,070
and protect wildlife,

433
00:18:25,120 --> 00:18:26,180
that's fine.

434
00:18:27,000 --> 00:18:27,980
But now,

435
00:18:28,380 --> 00:18:29,340
you can't even

436
00:18:29,370 --> 00:18:30,390
protect your own home.

437
00:18:30,390 --> 00:18:32,390
Why should you protect the animals?

438
00:18:46,550 --> 00:18:47,940
When Tashi was at school,

439
00:18:47,940 --> 00:18:48,960
he got into a fight

440
00:18:49,670 --> 00:18:50,810
because his classmates

441
00:18:50,810 --> 00:18:52,140
were talking about you,

442
00:18:53,420 --> 00:18:55,600
saying that you were eating
Tibetan antelope meat

443
00:18:55,600 --> 00:18:56,930
in the Uninhabited Zone

444
00:19:00,780 --> 00:19:02,460
He helped people sell jewelry

445
00:19:03,350 --> 00:19:04,530
and only got a share of

446
00:19:04,530 --> 00:19:05,590
over 100 yuan.

447
00:19:06,850 --> 00:19:07,820
I sent it all

448
00:19:07,850 --> 00:19:08,980
to Cisong's family.

449
00:19:10,500 --> 00:19:11,460
Tashi said

450
00:19:12,940 --> 00:19:15,140
he saved every cent and didn't spend any

451
00:19:16,980 --> 00:19:18,760
because he wanted to help me.

452
00:19:27,490 --> 00:19:29,430
If only we hadn't taken Tashi

453
00:19:31,500 --> 00:19:32,500
from my cousin's place

454
00:19:32,500 --> 00:19:33,900
back home.

455
00:20:09,650 --> 00:20:10,740
What a great photo.

456
00:20:11,550 --> 00:20:12,240
Thanks, brother.

457
00:20:12,240 --> 00:20:12,900
No problem.

458
00:20:14,270 --> 00:20:14,800
Brother,

459
00:20:14,860 --> 00:20:16,220
keep one for yourself.

460
00:20:19,880 --> 00:20:20,940
How about this one?

461
00:20:21,810 --> 00:20:22,310
Nice.

462
00:20:23,920 --> 00:20:24,450
Brother.

463
00:20:25,850 --> 00:20:26,330
When you go,

464
00:20:26,330 --> 00:20:27,660
don't just give photos.

465
00:20:27,980 --> 00:20:28,660
I know.

466
00:20:28,980 --> 00:20:30,710
I'll give some small gifts too.

467
00:20:31,090 --> 00:20:32,110
What small gifts?

468
00:20:32,220 --> 00:20:33,000
I mean...

469
00:20:33,020 --> 00:20:34,280
What are you two doing?

470
00:20:34,460 --> 00:20:35,720
Sneaking around here.

471
00:20:36,710 --> 00:20:37,510
No, no, no.

472
00:20:37,530 --> 00:20:38,390
Just chatting.

473
00:20:38,400 --> 00:20:39,090
You hang the clothes.

474
00:20:39,090 --> 00:20:39,890
It's nothing.

475
00:20:41,290 --> 00:20:42,290
Bro, go on.

476
00:20:42,400 --> 00:20:43,530
I mean,

477
00:20:43,610 --> 00:20:44,940
don't just give things.

478
00:20:45,270 --> 00:20:46,050
Borrow some.

479
00:20:46,590 --> 00:20:47,530
That way, you'll have another excuse

480
00:20:47,530 --> 00:20:48,400
to meet again.

481
00:20:50,220 --> 00:20:51,460
Eating together and borrowing books

482
00:20:51,460 --> 00:20:52,500
are two extremely

483
00:20:52,530 --> 00:20:53,590
flirtatious acts.

484
00:20:53,590 --> 00:20:54,880
Borrowing and returning,

485
00:20:54,880 --> 00:20:56,110
inviting and accepting.

486
00:20:56,110 --> 00:20:57,640
That's how a bond is formed.

487
00:20:58,290 --> 00:20:59,050
Yes, yes.

488
00:20:59,640 --> 00:21:00,610
You indeed know your ways.

489
00:21:00,610 --> 00:21:01,090
No, no.

490
00:21:01,380 --> 00:21:02,140
I learned it from "Fortress Besieged".

491
00:21:02,140 --> 00:21:03,440
I'll give you a copy next time.

492
00:21:03,440 --> 00:21:04,790
No, I'll give you two.

493
00:21:05,660 --> 00:21:07,100
Tuck a love letter inside

494
00:21:07,180 --> 00:21:08,380
and give it to Wangmu.

495
00:21:08,920 --> 00:21:09,460
Okay.

496
00:21:10,180 --> 00:21:11,430
What's okay about that?

497
00:21:11,430 --> 00:21:13,160
Can Wangmu even understand it?

498
00:21:13,750 --> 00:21:14,270
The Tibetan part,

499
00:21:14,270 --> 00:21:15,640
I had Sangba polish it.

500
00:21:15,740 --> 00:21:16,410
It's fine.

501
00:21:16,590 --> 00:21:18,250
I meant "Fortress Besieged".

502
00:21:19,050 --> 00:21:19,840
Oh, right.

503
00:21:19,920 --> 00:21:20,820
If you ask me,

504
00:21:21,350 --> 00:21:22,950
you should stop chasing her.

505
00:21:23,190 --> 00:21:24,590
What do you have to offer?

506
00:21:25,670 --> 00:21:27,130
Even if you do win her over,

507
00:21:27,220 --> 00:21:28,830
you go into the mountains for days,

508
00:21:28,830 --> 00:21:30,200
leaving her waiting outside.

509
00:21:30,200 --> 00:21:31,740
Bro, don't listen to her.

510
00:21:32,150 --> 00:21:32,770
I say,

511
00:21:32,790 --> 00:21:34,700
send the photo and letter together.

512
00:21:34,700 --> 00:21:35,480
You've revised it

513
00:21:35,480 --> 00:21:36,200
so many times anyway.

514
00:21:36,200 --> 00:21:38,200
It's more rigorous than my reports.

515
00:21:40,530 --> 00:21:41,180
Bai Ju.

516
00:21:41,870 --> 00:21:42,610
You have to face

517
00:21:42,610 --> 00:21:44,210
the diversity of this world.

518
00:21:44,550 --> 00:21:45,240
There are plenty of people

519
00:21:45,240 --> 00:21:46,000
worse off than him.

520
00:21:46,000 --> 00:21:47,410
How do they date?

521
00:21:48,350 --> 00:21:49,810
I don't know about others,

522
00:21:49,940 --> 00:21:50,480
but He Qingyuan

523
00:21:50,480 --> 00:21:53,140
has been bad at chasing girls
since high school.

524
00:21:53,550 --> 00:21:54,090
That class monitor of yours

525
00:21:54,090 --> 00:21:55,140
rejected you.

526
00:21:55,770 --> 00:21:56,310
You couldn't eat

527
00:21:56,310 --> 00:21:57,570
for months, could you?

528
00:21:59,440 --> 00:21:59,920
Six months.

529
00:21:59,920 --> 00:22:00,460
See?

530
00:22:01,500 --> 00:22:02,000
Well,

531
00:22:02,840 --> 00:22:04,860
you can't stop people from growing.

532
00:22:05,930 --> 00:22:07,680
The point is, how has he grown?

533
00:22:08,310 --> 00:22:09,290
When you were taking photos of Wangmu,

534
00:22:09,290 --> 00:22:10,150
didn't you see?

535
00:22:10,350 --> 00:22:10,900
He just stood there

536
00:22:10,900 --> 00:22:12,030
like a block of wood.

537
00:22:12,290 --> 00:22:13,090
Even for a photo with Wangmu,

538
00:22:13,090 --> 00:22:14,620
he didn't dare step closer.

539
00:22:15,010 --> 00:22:17,470
That's exactly why he needs encouragement.

540
00:22:18,240 --> 00:22:19,050
What do you know?

541
00:22:19,050 --> 00:22:21,180
You're just blindly encouraging him.

542
00:22:21,330 --> 00:22:22,320
We are all at the age

543
00:22:22,320 --> 00:22:23,780
to consider marriage now.

544
00:22:24,220 --> 00:22:25,400
Besides feelings,

545
00:22:25,650 --> 00:22:27,910
we must consider practical conditions.

546
00:22:27,960 --> 00:22:29,560
With his current situation,

547
00:22:29,570 --> 00:22:31,570
how can he provide her a stable life?

548
00:22:31,990 --> 00:22:32,850
Never mind him.

549
00:22:33,190 --> 00:22:34,210
Just look at Han.

550
00:22:34,720 --> 00:22:35,920
Isn't it obvious?

551
00:22:36,010 --> 00:22:36,970
Han had a blind date.

552
00:22:36,970 --> 00:22:37,850
He's pursuing free love.

553
00:22:37,850 --> 00:22:39,160
Can you compare the two?

554
00:22:39,160 --> 00:22:39,770
I think you are just

555
00:22:39,770 --> 00:22:40,830
enjoying the drama.

556
00:22:40,830 --> 00:22:41,850
Then according to you,

557
00:22:41,850 --> 00:22:42,570
the Mountain Patrol members

558
00:22:42,570 --> 00:22:44,370
should all stay single forever.

559
00:22:45,160 --> 00:22:46,130
I didn't say that.

560
00:22:46,130 --> 00:22:47,030
That's what you meant.

561
00:22:47,030 --> 00:22:47,640
I... I...

562
00:22:47,740 --> 00:22:48,610
Stop arguing.

563
00:22:49,010 --> 00:22:50,740
This is not worth arguing over.

564
00:22:52,330 --> 00:22:53,460
I'll think about it.

565
00:22:54,030 --> 00:22:54,890
Think about it.

566
00:22:56,030 --> 00:22:56,660
Thanks.

567
00:23:06,500 --> 00:23:07,480
You must send

568
00:23:07,510 --> 00:23:08,610
the love letter.

569
00:23:08,810 --> 00:23:09,660
Okay, okay.

570
00:23:19,350 --> 00:23:20,680
Is there anything else?

571
00:23:24,620 --> 00:23:26,280
You went a bit too far just now.

572
00:23:26,720 --> 00:23:27,850
I was stating facts.

573
00:23:27,880 --> 00:23:29,210
I know it's a fact.

574
00:23:29,850 --> 00:23:30,510
But it's also a fact

575
00:23:30,510 --> 00:23:32,240
that He Qingyuan likes Wangmu.

576
00:23:33,220 --> 00:23:34,050
True love

577
00:23:34,140 --> 00:23:34,950
can overcome

578
00:23:34,980 --> 00:23:36,360
all external difficulties.

579
00:23:36,360 --> 00:23:36,840
First,

580
00:23:37,440 --> 00:23:38,900
no time to spend together.

581
00:23:38,980 --> 00:23:39,530
Second,

582
00:23:39,850 --> 00:23:41,140
no financial foundation.

583
00:23:41,140 --> 00:23:42,240
How can this love begin?

584
00:23:42,240 --> 00:23:42,750
It's not just

585
00:23:42,750 --> 00:23:43,630
well-matched relationships

586
00:23:43,630 --> 00:23:44,820
that are worth starting.

587
00:23:44,820 --> 00:23:46,880
If He Qingyuan sends the love letter,

588
00:23:46,960 --> 00:23:48,660
at least he won't have regrets.

589
00:23:48,660 --> 00:23:49,640
Don't let He Qingyuan's

590
00:23:49,640 --> 00:23:51,170
rough appearance fool you.

591
00:23:51,310 --> 00:23:52,810
He's actually very fragile inside.

592
00:23:52,810 --> 00:23:53,900
You can irresponsibly

593
00:23:53,900 --> 00:23:54,250
egg him on,

594
00:23:54,250 --> 00:23:55,350
get him all worked up,

595
00:23:55,350 --> 00:23:56,590
and then just walk away.

596
00:23:56,590 --> 00:23:57,310
But I can't.

597
00:23:57,420 --> 00:23:58,370
Love is inherently

598
00:23:58,370 --> 00:23:59,700
full of uncertainties.

599
00:24:00,460 --> 00:24:01,180
No one can guarantee

600
00:24:01,180 --> 00:24:02,760
that effort leads to good results.

601
00:24:02,760 --> 00:24:04,010
I know you mean well for him,

602
00:24:04,010 --> 00:24:05,030
but you must also know,

603
00:24:05,030 --> 00:24:05,580
all love

604
00:24:05,610 --> 00:24:06,590
is an adventure.

605
00:24:06,850 --> 00:24:07,590
One should at least

606
00:24:07,590 --> 00:24:09,390
be honest about their feelings.

607
00:24:16,990 --> 00:24:17,850
Say something.

608
00:24:19,350 --> 00:24:20,030
Say what?

609
00:24:24,180 --> 00:24:25,420
Like I'm talking big again

610
00:24:25,420 --> 00:24:26,750
or something like that.

611
00:24:28,490 --> 00:24:29,240
You should talk less

612
00:24:29,240 --> 00:24:30,330
about honesty.

613
00:24:31,290 --> 00:24:32,250
Even when making a phone call,

614
00:24:32,250 --> 00:24:34,050
you don't dare to tell the truth.

615
00:24:35,350 --> 00:24:35,940
When you were in the county,

616
00:24:35,940 --> 00:24:36,500
you called your workplace,

617
00:24:36,500 --> 00:24:37,510
didn't you?

618
00:24:38,400 --> 00:24:39,050
Your creative leave

619
00:24:39,050 --> 00:24:40,050
is long overdue.

620
00:24:40,450 --> 00:24:42,910
The chief editor is rushing you back,
right?

621
00:24:45,270 --> 00:24:47,270
I didn't call the newspaper office.

622
00:24:47,790 --> 00:24:49,270
I called the paper mill.

623
00:24:51,100 --> 00:24:52,700
The paper mill is in Tianduo.

624
00:24:53,180 --> 00:24:54,400
The area code is 0982.

625
00:24:55,180 --> 00:24:56,680
You dialed 0971.

626
00:24:57,910 --> 00:24:59,710
That's the provincial capital.

627
00:25:20,280 --> 00:25:21,130
Tashi Delek.

628
00:25:23,920 --> 00:25:24,940
Tashi Delek.

629
00:25:38,400 --> 00:25:40,130
You must be tired from the trip.

630
00:25:40,510 --> 00:25:41,290
Tashi Delek.

631
00:25:43,310 --> 00:25:44,710
You came to find your son?

632
00:25:45,980 --> 00:25:47,440
I heard Cairen mention it.

633
00:25:47,720 --> 00:25:48,290
For the past two days,

634
00:25:48,290 --> 00:25:49,690
I've caused you trouble.

635
00:25:51,000 --> 00:25:52,130
These past few days,

636
00:25:52,570 --> 00:25:53,900
he's been staying here.

637
00:25:54,450 --> 00:25:55,520
Riding horses every day,

638
00:25:55,520 --> 00:25:56,980
herding sheep and cattle,

639
00:25:57,070 --> 00:25:58,670
and refusing to go to school.

640
00:25:59,090 --> 00:26:00,010
He's just a kid.

641
00:26:00,110 --> 00:26:01,510
Just throwing a tantrum.

642
00:26:01,970 --> 00:26:03,900
Newborn calves don't fear tigers,

643
00:26:03,900 --> 00:26:05,830
but grow horns and they fear sheep.

644
00:26:06,530 --> 00:26:07,130
It's fine.

645
00:26:07,360 --> 00:26:08,620
He'll get over it soon.

646
00:26:24,810 --> 00:26:25,830
This little calf

647
00:26:26,190 --> 00:26:27,190
is very stubborn.

648
00:26:28,160 --> 00:26:29,510
Who does he get

649
00:26:29,730 --> 00:26:30,730
that temper from?

650
00:26:39,940 --> 00:26:41,580
I heard many rumors

651
00:26:41,680 --> 00:26:43,220
about the Mountain Patrol.

652
00:26:44,510 --> 00:26:45,970
None of them are positive.

653
00:26:46,550 --> 00:26:47,680
They aren't rumors.

654
00:26:49,040 --> 00:26:50,340
Most of them are true.

655
00:26:51,740 --> 00:26:52,740
Recently,

656
00:26:53,220 --> 00:26:53,710
the Mountain Patrol

657
00:26:53,710 --> 00:26:55,070
has been through a lot.

658
00:26:57,410 --> 00:26:59,000
Ever since Dongzhiba died,

659
00:27:00,310 --> 00:27:02,510
Zhacuo's mother has been very worried.

660
00:27:03,730 --> 00:27:04,310
This time, Zhacuo

661
00:27:04,310 --> 00:27:05,710
is in the hospital again.

662
00:27:06,710 --> 00:27:08,360
She doesn't want her son

663
00:27:08,510 --> 00:27:09,910
to work with you anymore.

664
00:27:10,500 --> 00:27:11,630
It's too dangerous.

665
00:27:15,270 --> 00:27:16,270
What do you think?

666
00:27:18,000 --> 00:27:18,870
You were the one who handed him over

667
00:27:18,870 --> 00:27:19,890
to me back then,

668
00:27:20,600 --> 00:27:22,200
asking me to discipline him.

669
00:27:25,140 --> 00:27:26,350
Now, Zhacuo's mother and I

670
00:27:26,350 --> 00:27:27,280
are getting old.

671
00:27:28,510 --> 00:27:30,180
We can't handle the pasture work.

672
00:27:30,180 --> 00:27:32,110
We're short on money and manpower.

673
00:27:33,550 --> 00:27:34,750
We talked it over.

674
00:27:36,090 --> 00:27:37,550
We want Zhacuo to come back

675
00:27:38,040 --> 00:27:39,570
to help manage the pasture.

676
00:27:41,250 --> 00:27:41,700
Right.

677
00:27:42,670 --> 00:27:43,530
I understand.

678
00:27:45,330 --> 00:27:46,460
But regarding this,

679
00:27:47,090 --> 00:27:47,790
I still need to ask

680
00:27:47,790 --> 00:27:49,010
what Zhacuo wants.

681
00:27:49,720 --> 00:27:51,050
If he wants to come back,

682
00:27:51,640 --> 00:27:52,570
I won't stop him.

683
00:27:56,000 --> 00:27:56,530
Alright.

684
00:27:57,210 --> 00:27:57,860
Alright.

685
00:27:59,850 --> 00:28:00,290
Here.

686
00:28:04,310 --> 00:28:05,170
What about you?

687
00:28:06,030 --> 00:28:07,560
Are you going to keep going?

688
00:28:08,210 --> 00:28:09,140
What do you mean?

689
00:28:12,980 --> 00:28:14,420
A lot of friends

690
00:28:15,090 --> 00:28:17,020
don't associate with you anymore.

691
00:28:18,420 --> 00:28:19,820
I heard someone out there

692
00:28:19,990 --> 00:28:21,660
wants your head.

693
00:28:22,660 --> 00:28:24,260
Worth two million, isn't it?

694
00:28:25,330 --> 00:28:25,970
That much?

695
00:28:29,290 --> 00:28:30,750
Aren't you short on money?

696
00:28:31,640 --> 00:28:33,100
I'll just give you my head.

697
00:28:37,610 --> 00:28:38,750
Here, drink some tea.

698
00:28:38,750 --> 00:28:39,440
Drink.

699
00:28:53,700 --> 00:28:54,090
Hyah!

700
00:28:57,390 --> 00:28:58,180
I watched you just now.

701
00:28:58,180 --> 00:28:59,380
You ride pretty well,

702
00:29:00,660 --> 00:29:01,920
even better than me.

703
00:29:06,700 --> 00:29:07,700
Your mother said,

704
00:29:08,800 --> 00:29:09,660
you're feeding

705
00:29:09,700 --> 00:29:11,010
the horses well too.

706
00:29:12,700 --> 00:29:13,610
Jiongxi's coat

707
00:29:13,650 --> 00:29:15,450
seems much shinier than before.

708
00:29:20,290 --> 00:29:21,820
You're herding sheep here.

709
00:29:22,460 --> 00:29:22,900
Do you not want

710
00:29:22,900 --> 00:29:24,230
to go to school anymore?

711
00:29:24,790 --> 00:29:26,520
I'm no good at studying anyway.

712
00:29:26,790 --> 00:29:28,050
I'd rather herd sheep.

713
00:29:32,190 --> 00:29:33,990
You don't even want to come home?

714
00:29:34,530 --> 00:29:36,400
You don't come home either, do you?

715
00:29:36,400 --> 00:29:37,670
I have work to do.

716
00:29:38,690 --> 00:29:39,820
What's your excuse?

717
00:29:45,050 --> 00:29:46,700
You're at the age for school.

718
00:29:47,700 --> 00:29:48,960
You need to study hard.

719
00:29:49,880 --> 00:29:51,080
I don't want to study.

720
00:29:52,110 --> 00:29:53,570
Then what do you want to do?

721
00:29:56,030 --> 00:29:56,760
I don't know.

722
00:29:58,250 --> 00:29:59,510
Herding sheep is fine.

723
00:30:05,160 --> 00:30:06,450
I actually envy you

724
00:30:07,180 --> 00:30:08,400
right now.

725
00:30:10,790 --> 00:30:12,520
Not knowing what you want to do.

726
00:30:14,010 --> 00:30:15,220
Not having found that one thing

727
00:30:15,220 --> 00:30:17,080
you absolutely must accomplish.

728
00:30:19,830 --> 00:30:21,290
Once that thing appears,

729
00:30:22,850 --> 00:30:24,460
you will spend all your time

730
00:30:24,480 --> 00:30:25,650
on it.

731
00:30:26,770 --> 00:30:28,180
Everything else

732
00:30:28,270 --> 00:30:29,530
won't matter anymore.

733
00:30:31,030 --> 00:30:32,810
Family and relatives

734
00:30:33,590 --> 00:30:34,850
will all be neglected.

735
00:30:36,200 --> 00:30:36,710
Even if

736
00:30:36,740 --> 00:30:37,640
I had something I wanted to do,

737
00:30:37,640 --> 00:30:38,900
I wouldn't be like you.

738
00:30:46,830 --> 00:30:47,350
You'd better

739
00:30:47,350 --> 00:30:48,510
not become like me.

740
00:30:55,330 --> 00:30:55,860
Let's go.

741
00:30:56,790 --> 00:30:57,790
Come home with me.

742
00:31:03,440 --> 00:31:04,300
How about this?

743
00:31:05,550 --> 00:31:06,570
Let's have a race.

744
00:31:07,180 --> 00:31:09,510
See who gets to the top of that slope
first.

745
00:31:09,790 --> 00:31:10,700
If I win,

746
00:31:11,400 --> 00:31:12,600
you come home with me.

747
00:31:14,570 --> 00:31:15,090
Fine.

748
00:31:18,740 --> 00:31:20,200
But I want to ride Jiongxi.

749
00:31:24,740 --> 00:31:25,200
Okay.

750
00:31:27,000 --> 00:31:27,330
Hyah!

751
00:31:27,440 --> 00:31:27,770
Hyah!

752
00:31:51,700 --> 00:31:53,090
I left Jiongxi there.

753
00:31:53,640 --> 00:31:54,690
You can walk back.

754
00:31:57,550 --> 00:31:58,290
Hyah! Hyah!

755
00:32:08,480 --> 00:32:09,280
Wangmu.

756
00:32:09,950 --> 00:32:11,820
Did the instant noodles arrive?

757
00:32:12,600 --> 00:32:14,530
They've been selling well lately.

758
00:32:15,130 --> 00:32:17,060
Mom, no instant noodles this time.

759
00:32:17,570 --> 00:32:19,170
We didn't have enough money.

760
00:32:19,270 --> 00:32:21,000
Why wasn't there enough money?

761
00:32:21,660 --> 00:32:23,160
The accounts from last time

762
00:32:23,160 --> 00:32:24,510
didn't balance.

763
00:32:26,960 --> 00:32:28,140
It's okay.

764
00:32:28,610 --> 00:32:29,550
It's fine.

765
00:32:41,530 --> 00:32:42,660
Pay half first.

766
00:32:43,180 --> 00:32:43,850
The rest

767
00:32:43,880 --> 00:32:45,080
can be paid next time.

768
00:32:50,780 --> 00:32:51,350
Wait.

769
00:32:55,690 --> 00:32:56,290
Take this.

770
00:32:56,570 --> 00:32:57,380
I can't.

771
00:32:58,310 --> 00:32:59,400
This isn't cheap.

772
00:32:59,870 --> 00:33:01,070
It's about to expire.

773
00:33:01,200 --> 00:33:02,200
No one will buy it.

774
00:33:02,250 --> 00:33:03,980
You're helping me get rid of it.

775
00:33:08,850 --> 00:33:09,580
Just take it.

776
00:33:16,700 --> 00:33:17,570
Thank you.

777
00:33:18,620 --> 00:33:21,020
I'm always benefiting from your kindness.

778
00:33:21,140 --> 00:33:22,000
It's nothing.

779
00:33:22,450 --> 00:33:23,980
You're the ones helping me.

780
00:33:30,760 --> 00:33:31,390
Go on now.

781
00:33:42,240 --> 00:33:43,040
What's wrong?

782
00:33:48,240 --> 00:33:49,090
The photos from last time

783
00:33:49,090 --> 00:33:50,330
have been developed.

784
00:34:00,950 --> 00:34:02,520
You made my eyes look so big.

785
00:34:04,500 --> 00:34:05,510
So shiny.

786
00:34:07,370 --> 00:34:07,970
Your eyes

787
00:34:08,000 --> 00:34:09,460
are naturally beautiful.

788
00:34:22,210 --> 00:34:22,800
Wangmu.

789
00:34:25,800 --> 00:34:27,199
I have something for you.

790
00:34:32,969 --> 00:34:33,590
Reading?

791
00:34:39,550 --> 00:34:40,280
How did it go?

792
00:34:40,940 --> 00:34:41,840
How did what go?

793
00:34:42,100 --> 00:34:43,300
Did you give it to her?

794
00:34:43,650 --> 00:34:44,400
I did.

795
00:34:44,780 --> 00:34:45,710
Wangmu liked it.

796
00:34:45,820 --> 00:34:46,320
She said you

797
00:34:46,320 --> 00:34:48,050
made her look good in the photo.

798
00:34:48,500 --> 00:34:49,050
What?

799
00:34:49,670 --> 00:34:51,000
I meant the love letter.

800
00:34:52,900 --> 00:34:53,980
That goes without saying.

801
00:34:53,980 --> 00:34:54,780
That's right.

802
00:34:55,130 --> 00:34:56,280
You should listen to me.

803
00:34:56,280 --> 00:34:57,500
It would be bad if you listened to Bai Ju.

804
00:34:57,500 --> 00:34:58,190
Wangmu gave this.

805
00:34:58,190 --> 00:34:58,690
Thanks.

806
00:35:00,420 --> 00:35:01,750
I want that Wanziqianhong cream.

807
00:35:01,750 --> 00:35:02,880
Did you buy it for me?

808
00:35:04,300 --> 00:35:05,170
I forgot about it.

809
00:35:05,170 --> 00:35:06,030
-I’m sorry.
-You…

810
00:35:06,030 --> 00:35:07,300
I'll definitely remember next time.

811
00:35:07,300 --> 00:35:08,030
Definitely.

812
00:35:08,070 --> 00:35:09,330
You are unbelievable.

813
00:35:09,500 --> 00:35:10,140
Your head

814
00:35:10,170 --> 00:35:11,830
is just full of chasing girls.

815
00:35:12,190 --> 00:35:13,000
Next time...

816
00:35:13,030 --> 00:35:14,500
I'll remember to buy it for you.

817
00:35:14,500 --> 00:35:15,010
Thanks.

818
00:35:43,670 --> 00:35:44,670
It smells good.

819
00:35:49,070 --> 00:35:50,280
Mom's hands

820
00:35:50,510 --> 00:35:51,280
are so smooth

821
00:35:51,400 --> 00:35:52,470
like a little lamb

822
00:35:52,500 --> 00:35:53,980
that you can't hold onto.

823
00:36:01,430 --> 00:36:02,470
Bai Shao, hurry up.

824
00:36:02,470 --> 00:36:03,350
Let's go.

825
00:36:04,510 --> 00:36:05,110
Bai Shao.

826
00:36:07,480 --> 00:36:08,140
Who is that?

827
00:36:09,050 --> 00:36:10,340
Why are you here?

828
00:36:10,730 --> 00:36:11,820
Nice clothes.

829
00:36:11,860 --> 00:36:13,120
Where did you get them?

830
00:36:17,320 --> 00:36:18,650
What are you doing here?

831
00:36:18,980 --> 00:36:20,240
Let's go watch a video.

832
00:36:20,590 --> 00:36:21,480
Watch a video?

833
00:36:22,030 --> 00:36:22,820
Now?

834
00:36:24,590 --> 00:36:25,460
Not today.

835
00:36:25,510 --> 00:36:26,470
I have plans with colleagues.

836
00:36:26,470 --> 00:36:27,530
We're going to eat.

837
00:36:27,840 --> 00:36:29,230
You can eat anytime.

838
00:36:30,940 --> 00:36:32,150
Bai Shao is busy today.

839
00:36:32,150 --> 00:36:32,650
She can't...

840
00:36:32,650 --> 00:36:33,850
...eat with you guys.

841
00:36:34,910 --> 00:36:36,230
Bai Shao, who is this?

842
00:36:37,050 --> 00:36:38,110
I'm her boyfriend.

843
00:36:38,690 --> 00:36:39,420
Boyfriend?

844
00:36:39,910 --> 00:36:41,210
We'll be going then.

845
00:36:41,240 --> 00:36:42,260
Bye, Ju.

846
00:36:45,150 --> 00:36:45,760
Let's go.

847
00:36:50,040 --> 00:36:50,640
Go on.

848
00:37:00,090 --> 00:37:01,690
Chingmy Yau is so beautiful.

849
00:37:02,070 --> 00:37:03,130
Her eyes are round.

850
00:37:03,590 --> 00:37:04,790
Her face is round too.

851
00:37:05,400 --> 00:37:06,730
She looks a bit like you.

852
00:37:08,610 --> 00:37:09,210
Really?

853
00:37:09,440 --> 00:37:10,000
Yeah.

854
00:37:10,460 --> 00:37:12,190
Don't you like buying clothes?

855
00:37:12,210 --> 00:37:13,160
Next time, you can try

856
00:37:13,160 --> 00:37:14,560
that pink color she wore.

857
00:37:16,570 --> 00:37:17,970
I didn't notice just now.

858
00:37:18,040 --> 00:37:19,260
And Jacky Cheung running away.

859
00:37:19,260 --> 00:37:20,390
That was hilarious.

860
00:37:20,510 --> 00:37:21,730
How did they do that?

861
00:37:23,710 --> 00:37:24,680
I... today...

862
00:37:25,940 --> 00:37:27,470
Can't you tell I'm unhappy?

863
00:37:29,030 --> 00:37:29,960
You're unhappy?

864
00:37:30,210 --> 00:37:31,210
What do you think?

865
00:37:32,130 --> 00:37:32,920
I didn't notice.

866
00:37:32,920 --> 00:37:34,580
I was just watching the movie.

867
00:37:35,050 --> 00:37:36,110
If you're unhappy,

868
00:37:36,130 --> 00:37:37,150
you can tell me.

869
00:37:37,670 --> 00:37:38,480
I'm a person

870
00:37:38,590 --> 00:37:39,590
who is straightforward.

871
00:37:39,590 --> 00:37:40,800
I can't read minds.

872
00:37:42,760 --> 00:37:43,190
Fine.

873
00:37:43,820 --> 00:37:44,900
I'll be direct.

874
00:37:46,570 --> 00:37:47,830
Let's just be friends.

875
00:37:49,090 --> 00:37:49,650
Aren't we

876
00:37:49,680 --> 00:37:50,680
dating right now?

877
00:37:50,700 --> 00:37:52,320
I mean just friends.

878
00:37:54,650 --> 00:37:56,030
We're not a good match.

879
00:37:56,510 --> 00:37:58,170
We have nothing to talk about.

880
00:38:00,170 --> 00:38:00,920
You didn't like

881
00:38:00,920 --> 00:38:02,260
the movie just now, did you?

882
00:38:02,260 --> 00:38:03,440
We'll pick another one next time.

883
00:38:03,440 --> 00:38:04,190
Whatever you want to watch.

884
00:38:04,190 --> 00:38:04,840
That opera one.

885
00:38:04,840 --> 00:38:06,190
I'm not talking about the movie.

886
00:38:06,190 --> 00:38:07,390
I'm talking about us.

887
00:38:07,860 --> 00:38:09,520
I think we're great together.

888
00:38:10,380 --> 00:38:10,900
Look at us.

889
00:38:10,900 --> 00:38:12,360
Our outfits match so well.

890
00:38:12,440 --> 00:38:12,980
And now,

891
00:38:13,010 --> 00:38:13,590
thanks to you,

892
00:38:13,590 --> 00:38:14,670
I'm really into fashion.

893
00:38:14,670 --> 00:38:15,090
Really.

894
00:38:15,090 --> 00:38:16,490
That's all superficial.

895
00:38:16,510 --> 00:38:17,520
Don't you care quite a lot

896
00:38:17,520 --> 00:38:18,300
about appearances?

897
00:38:18,300 --> 00:38:20,100
I care about what's inside, too.

898
00:38:21,110 --> 00:38:21,650
Do you know what kind

899
00:38:21,650 --> 00:38:22,260
of movies I like?

900
00:38:22,260 --> 00:38:22,940
Do you know?

901
00:38:23,030 --> 00:38:23,940
Do you know why I like them?

902
00:38:23,940 --> 00:38:24,740
Do you know?

903
00:38:26,260 --> 00:38:27,020
Just now during the movie,

904
00:38:27,020 --> 00:38:27,920
everyone was laughing.

905
00:38:27,920 --> 00:38:28,630
I was the only one not laughing.

906
00:38:28,630 --> 00:38:29,780
Did you notice?

907
00:38:34,650 --> 00:38:36,180
It's still about the movie.

908
00:38:36,340 --> 00:38:37,900
No, no.

909
00:38:40,000 --> 00:38:41,580
It's that when I'm with you,

910
00:38:41,730 --> 00:38:42,450
I don't feel like

911
00:38:42,450 --> 00:38:43,580
we're dating at all.

912
00:38:43,940 --> 00:38:44,550
Instead, I feel like

913
00:38:44,550 --> 00:38:45,210
I'm an elder sister

914
00:38:45,210 --> 00:38:46,190
and you're a little brother.

915
00:38:46,190 --> 00:38:47,360
You are older than me.

916
00:38:47,360 --> 00:38:47,920
Can you just let me

917
00:38:47,920 --> 00:38:48,760
finish?

918
00:38:49,710 --> 00:38:50,150
Sure.

919
00:38:50,470 --> 00:38:52,020
That's the point.

920
00:38:52,440 --> 00:38:53,010
An older woman and a younger man.

921
00:38:53,010 --> 00:38:53,710
This kind of relationship

922
00:38:53,710 --> 00:38:55,260
really might not suit me.

923
00:38:55,380 --> 00:38:56,340
I already have a brother at home

924
00:38:56,340 --> 00:38:57,380
who gives me enough

925
00:38:57,380 --> 00:38:58,240
to worry about.

926
00:38:58,340 --> 00:38:59,280
I don't want to be a big sister

927
00:38:59,280 --> 00:39:00,740
when I'm dating.

928
00:39:06,070 --> 00:39:06,710
Okay.

929
00:39:08,530 --> 00:39:09,930
Then let's switch roles.

930
00:39:10,030 --> 00:39:12,760
I'll be the big brother,
you be the little sister.

931
00:39:14,630 --> 00:39:15,880
I have a brother.

932
00:39:16,320 --> 00:39:18,120
I don't need you to be my brother.

933
00:39:23,450 --> 00:39:25,310
Then I'll be your second brother.

934
00:40:04,340 --> 00:40:05,050
Who am I?

935
00:40:07,010 --> 00:40:07,730
Bai Ju.

936
00:40:08,810 --> 00:40:10,010
I'm a police officer.

937
00:40:11,820 --> 00:40:12,350
Let's go.

938
00:40:22,400 --> 00:40:22,970
Sis.

939
00:40:23,650 --> 00:40:24,380
You're back.

940
00:40:25,590 --> 00:40:26,860
Who let you play with the car?

941
00:40:26,860 --> 00:40:27,790
You'll break it.

942
00:40:28,050 --> 00:40:28,710
I won't, Ju.

943
00:40:29,000 --> 00:40:30,030
Han taught me.

944
00:40:30,280 --> 00:40:31,410
He's an amateur too.

945
00:40:31,820 --> 00:40:33,130
Don't play with it anymore.

946
00:40:33,130 --> 00:40:33,780
Okay.

947
00:40:34,290 --> 00:40:34,980
Put it away.

948
00:40:35,110 --> 00:40:35,590
Okay.

949
00:40:38,150 --> 00:40:39,010
Come on, Tashi.

950
00:40:39,270 --> 00:40:39,990
Let me show you around

951
00:40:39,990 --> 00:40:40,640
our base.

952
00:40:43,680 --> 00:40:44,480
What's wrong?

953
00:40:44,510 --> 00:40:45,840
What's so good about it?

954
00:40:46,620 --> 00:40:47,620
I don't want to go.

955
00:40:53,400 --> 00:40:53,960
Fine.

956
00:40:54,420 --> 00:40:56,220
Then play in the yard for a while.

957
00:40:59,090 --> 00:40:59,750
Zhang Yang,

958
00:41:00,070 --> 00:41:01,070
keep him company.

959
00:41:01,420 --> 00:41:01,980
Sure.

960
00:41:09,120 --> 00:41:10,780
Where's the Captain? Is he in?

961
00:41:11,550 --> 00:41:12,320
He went out.

962
00:41:12,420 --> 00:41:13,220
What's wrong?

963
00:41:14,150 --> 00:41:14,800
That guy.

964
00:41:15,280 --> 00:41:15,840
I went through so much trouble

965
00:41:15,840 --> 00:41:17,040
to bring his son back,

966
00:41:17,300 --> 00:41:18,380
and he ran off.

967
00:41:30,670 --> 00:41:32,070
What are you looking for?

968
00:41:32,650 --> 00:41:34,450
Something to entertain the kid.

969
00:41:39,570 --> 00:41:40,190
Well,

970
00:41:40,210 --> 00:41:41,050
let him play with a gun.

971
00:41:41,050 --> 00:41:42,280
Boys love guns.

972
00:41:43,730 --> 00:41:44,320
Sure.

973
00:41:44,880 --> 00:41:46,080
I'll give him the gun,

974
00:41:46,230 --> 00:41:47,080
lock you two in the room,

975
00:41:47,080 --> 00:41:48,480
and you can play with him.

976
00:41:48,590 --> 00:41:49,670
Forget I said that.

977
00:41:49,820 --> 00:41:51,340
I wasn't thinking.

978
00:41:57,520 --> 00:41:58,520
Do you like cars?

979
00:41:59,860 --> 00:42:01,110
All men like cars.

980
00:42:01,650 --> 00:42:02,650
I don't.

981
00:42:03,320 --> 00:42:04,510
Grass crushed by cars

982
00:42:04,510 --> 00:42:06,170
won't grow back the next year.

983
00:42:06,630 --> 00:42:07,830
Then what do you like?

984
00:42:07,980 --> 00:42:08,800
I like horses.

985
00:42:09,280 --> 00:42:11,080
What's so special about horses?

986
00:42:11,270 --> 00:42:12,470
They're everywhere.

987
00:42:12,550 --> 00:42:13,750
I like riding horses.

988
00:42:13,820 --> 00:42:14,880
Horses can't talk,

989
00:42:15,210 --> 00:42:16,130
but being with them

990
00:42:16,130 --> 00:42:18,590
is more comfortable than
being with people.

991
00:42:19,610 --> 00:42:20,570
I'm Zhang Yang.

992
00:42:21,400 --> 00:42:22,800
You can call me Xiaoyang.

993
00:42:23,630 --> 00:42:24,820
Yang as in 'sandstorm'.

994
00:42:24,820 --> 00:42:26,130
Yang as in 'setting sail'.

995
00:42:26,130 --> 00:42:26,820
I know.

996
00:42:28,280 --> 00:42:29,280
What's your name?

997
00:42:29,350 --> 00:42:29,960
Tashi.

998
00:42:31,690 --> 00:42:32,950
Captain Duojie's son.

999
00:42:34,170 --> 00:42:35,770
Captain Duojie is a good man.

1000
00:42:36,900 --> 00:42:37,450
He's the one

1001
00:42:37,450 --> 00:42:38,630
who let me stay here.

1002
00:42:45,080 --> 00:42:47,100
His dad drives every day.

1003
00:42:47,170 --> 00:42:47,830
He's definitely not

1004
00:42:47,830 --> 00:42:49,220
interested in cars.

1005
00:42:52,410 --> 00:42:53,320
What should we do then?

1006
00:42:53,320 --> 00:42:54,170
Send him back?

1007
00:42:56,530 --> 00:42:57,190
You oaf.

1008
00:42:58,630 --> 00:42:59,570
I can tell you've never done

1009
00:42:59,570 --> 00:43:00,630
any counseling.
